-----------ALGO WITH Example-------------
Algorithm: Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock

Problem:
Given an array where prices[i] is the stock price on day i,
find the maximum profit from buying once and selling once.

Idea:
Track the cheapest price seen so far.
For each day, calculate the profit if we sell on that day.
Update the maximum profit accordingly.

Steps:
1. If the array has fewer than 2 prices, return 0.

2. Initialize:
      cheap = ∞        (minimum price seen so far)
      max_p = 0        (maximum profit)

3. Traverse the price list.

4. For each price i:
      a) If i is smaller than cheap
            update cheap = i   (buy at this price)

      b) Otherwise
            compute profit = i - cheap
            update max_p = max(max_p, profit)

5. After the loop return max_p.


Example:

prices = [7,1,5,3,6,4]


Step-by-step table

Day | Price | Cheapest So Far | Profit if Sold Today | Max Profit
------------------------------------------------------------------
0   | 7     | 7               | 0                    | 0
1   | 1     | 1               | 0                    | 0
2   | 5     | 1               | 4 (5-1)              | 4
3   | 3     | 1               | 2 (3-1)              | 4
4   | 6     | 1               | 5 (6-1)              | 5
5   | 4     | 1               | 3 (4-1)              | 5


Best Action:
Buy at price = 1 (day 1)
Sell at price = 6 (day 4)

Maximum Profit = 5


Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
